## Do's and Don'ts

### Do's

- ✓ Present results objectively without interpretation
- ✓ Include quantitative data with statistics
- ✓ Reference all figures and tables
- ✓ Use consistent terminology
- ✓ Report negative results
- ✓ Provide sample sizes
- ✓ Use past tense for findings
- ✓ Alternate between active and passive voice

### Don'ts

- ✗ Interpret results (save for Discussion)
- ✗ Include methods details
- ✗ Cite literature (except for methods)
- ✗ Use vague terms ("high", "low", "many")
- ✗ Overuse "we" (target: ≤30%)
- ✗ Include raw data (use figures/tables)
- ✗ Repeat figure captions verbatim
- ✗ Speculate about mechanisms

